HEADWORD: Etiolin
<hw>E"ti*o*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Etiolate</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A yellowish coloring
matter found in plants grown in darkness, which is supposed to be an
antecedent condition of chlorophyll.</def> <rj><au>Encyc.
Brit.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
